cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.CE, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the use of reduced-order models in control systems and introduces a new method for predicting errors and dimensions of these models. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper employs Gaussian Processes and Artificial Neural Networks to construct approximations of multivariate mappings, which are used to predict the errors and dimensions of reduced-order models. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper presents numerical results with a viscous Burgers model to illustrate the performance of the proposed method. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper discusses the application of reduced-order models in computational engineering and presents a new method for predicting their errors and dimensions. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the scalability challenges of the proposed method and suggests ways to address them, which involves designing efficient algorithms and data structures.
